Thanks.</description><pubDate>Tue, 10 Feb 2015 22:03:06 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/5444/using-only-one-paneltray-when-using-i3-with-kde/</guid></item><item><title>Answer by ANOKNUSA for &lt;p&gt;I recently started using i3 with KDE to let KDE handle all the boring details, but now I can't make the tray working as I wanted. Basically I want to use only one tray -- either i3s or KDEs tray, but not both. Currently for some reason desktops are showing up in i3 tray, but applications are placed on Plasma's. Any ideas how do I remove one of them and let the other one handle all the things.&lt;/p&gt;

