&lt;p&gt;Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;
 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/5444/using-only-one-paneltray-when-using-i3-with-kde/?answer=5446#post-id-5446</link><description>Have a look at [Section 5](http://i3wm.org/docs/userguide.html#_configuring_i3bar) of the User's Guide. You can hide the entire bar, or just the system tray---whichever you'd like. Or you can remove the Plasma panel from KDE.</description><pubDate>Thu, 12 Feb 2015 21:23:20 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/5444/using-only-one-paneltray-when-using-i3-with-kde/?answer=5446#post-id-5446</guid></item></channel></rss>